               <p>ROBERT PENFOLD. On the 15th of April, about ten minutes past seven in the morning, I was unloading a coal-waggon in <placeName id="t18300415-364-crimeloc1970">Tower-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-364-crimeloc1970" type="placeName" value="Tower-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-364-crimeloc1970" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-364-off1968 t18300415-364-crimeloc1970"></join>; I took off my hat, and my handkerchief was in it - I put it on the premises while I went down with a sack of coals; when I came up a gentleman's son said, "Either you, or your mate, have lost a handkerchief;" and he showed me the prisoner in Mark-lane - there were four persons in company; he was the stoutest of them - I took him, and found my handkerchief in his bosom; this is it - I know it by a darn, and by the pattern: I gave it to the officer - it was as I had pulled it off my neck; I suppose I found it on him in about twenty minutes after I first put it down - we had unloaded one waggon; the prisoner's companions had parted from him, before I got up to him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It was given me by the three men, who told me to put it round my neck; I put it in my bosom, and gave it to the gentleman.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-364-person2998">
                  JOHN 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18300415-364-person2998" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-364-person2998" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-364-person2998" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took charge of the prisoner - he said it was given to him by one of the three men he had come from Greenwich fair with.</p>


